Jf/XqJalQpFK3KtU6WatCIW9WaTW9A15U0BMeG/QrTAgJukRD9Icxv1x8HwRQSQRD5g6rWCS4erlO3CJoEEhPfHHi7FenJa1tPR7fpL/tzeAXkO%2bDQO4oR5HE4FsIvgU8/X1edFNHAn%2bb5e%2bJwPh0Buhr6G/%2bBf9/ALRdsaiBMsLfAAAAAElFTkSuQmCC' /%3e%3c/svg%3e\" width=\"433\" alt=\"Business Tools icon on the Launchpad\" data-srcset=\"/assets/static/business-tools.3be3581.25511b91bfcc134e947ed8ccab5919c3.png 433w\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 433px) 100vw, 433px\" data-src=\"/assets/static/business-tools.3be3581.25511b91bfcc134e947ed8ccab5919c3.png\"><noscript><img class=\"g-image g-image--lazy g-image--loaded\" src=\"/assets/static/business-tools.3be3581.25511b91bfcc134e947ed8ccab5919c3.png\" width=\"433\" alt=\"Business Tools icon on the Launchpad\"></noscript></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Commerce Business Tools runs off localhost</strong></p>\n<p>The install script (Deploy-Sitecore-Commerce.ps1) provided by Sitecore installs the Business tools to run off <a href=\"https://localhost:4000/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">https://localhost:4000/</a>. There's no top-level parameter to change this. Instead, it is set in each application's SIF config file. It would be nice to see this added in future updates to Commerce to make configuring a public URL easier.</p>\n<p>To make Commerce Business Tools work on your public accessible host you'll need to:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Dig through the JSON configuration files of the various applications Commerce installed.</li>\n<li>Update the <em>Link</em> field of the core database item</li>\n<li><code>/sitecore/client/Applications/Launchpad/PageSettings/Buttons/Commerce/BusinessTools</code></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>New Commerce Chunk</strong></p>\n<p>The ribbon in the Content Editor has a new Commerce chunk, this is very useful to know about (see below).</p>\n<p><img class=\"g-image g-image--lazy g-image--loading\" src=\"data:image/svg+xml,%3csvg fill='none' viewBox='0 0 1129 180' xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg' xmlns:xlink='http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink'%3e%3cdefs%3e%3cfilter id='__svg-blur-10a5f976d005ac091518649523fc5ce0'%3e%3cfeGaussianBlur in='SourceGraphic' stdDeviation='40'/%3e%3c/filter%3e%3c/defs%3e%3cimage x='0' y='0' filter='url(%23__svg-blur-10a5f976d005ac091518649523fc5ce0)' width='1129' height='180' xlink:href='data:image/jpeg%3bbase64%%2bNFfEaAAUAAA7CKZCmMBbzuXlyW7HUorFRgNelh8Uh3Y/aR03/kK%2bJABsHp4tftHOPFD7jys2mZOXmfrnfp5jwpmA16g2STIVu9rQGhYRIA//2Q==' /%3e%3c/svg%3e\" width=\"1129\" alt=\"New commerce chunk in the content editor ribbon\" data-srcset=\"/assets/static/commerce-toolbar.82a2fbd.2a7988b877d9183c47a5a5b0f6bc9aa4.jpg 480w, /assets/static/commerce-toolbar.c92d2d3.2a7988b877d9183c47a5a5b0f6bc9aa4.jpg 1129w\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 1129px) 100vw, 1129px\" data-src=\"/assets/static/commerce-toolbar.c92d2d3.2a7988b877d9183c47a5a5b0f6bc9aa4.jpg\"><noscript><img class=\"g-image g-image--lazy g-image--loaded\" src=\"/assets/static/commerce-toolbar.c92d2d3.2a7988b877d9183c47a5a5b0f6bc9aa4.jpg\" width=\"1129\" alt=\"New commerce chunk in the content editor ribbon\"></noscript></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Getting new categories / products to show in the content editor</strong></p>\n<p>The section of the tree <code>/sitecore/Commerce/Catalog Management</code> dynamically creates items mimicking the\nstructure of your catalog. This allows them to be used as datasources. Before new categories and products appear,\nyou need to clear the commerce cache.</p>\n<p>To do this, click the <em>Refresh Commerce Cache</em> button within the new <em>Commerce</em> chunk. Then refresh the tree\nand the new items will appear.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Adding a new Catalog</strong></p>\n<p>New catalogs won't show in the <em>Catalog Management</em> section of the content editor by default. To configure which\ncatalogs appear, edit the <em>Selected Catalogs</em> field on the item <code>/sitecore/Commerce/Catalog Management/Catalogs</code>.</p>\n<p><img class=\"g-image g-image--lazy g-image--loading\" src=\"data:image/svg+xml,%3csvg fill='none' viewBox='0 0 320 174' xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg' xmlns:xlink='http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink'%3e%3cdefs%3e%3cfilter id='__svg-blur-a0e7d0b05abe249202263c31b19d6245'%3e%3cfeGaussianBlur in='SourceGraphic' stdDeviation='40'/%3e%3c/filter%3e%3c/defs%3e%3cimage x='0' y='0' filter='url(%23__svg-blur-a0e7d0b05abe249202263c31b19d6245)' width='320' height='174' xlink:href='data:image/jpeg%3bbase64%%2bA4fqjf8A76qRGRjV7dWm3qpHRK8nh%2b1/RyeydEryeHrX9HJ7K28dXWGVrH2e9oIJz7QEDzWyZZuyA/zCrKn/AESvJ4etf0cnsnRK8nh61/RyeyuAJZu2AjdzBeTLOBup8T%2b8IKg9EryeHrX9HJ7LqWVde2mWnZLm3ctqF0czTPJJTvLXdYHEDKMoHmVbJEGhLO1lfO0180RbAHbNsGZrOsOvjhvPZh3YoKxrNnI%2b2InRuLmgGmwxP9jBd2j%2bV91mQcKzM9VL%2bDawqGxFu0aadoOGHAnvK7mRvKNEDWhxIABPE4cVKCMjeUaJkbyjRSiCMjeUaLHO1ohcQBosqx1HyX%2bSDQDiOBIU53cx1REDO7mOqZ3cx1REDO7mOqZ3cx1REDO7mOqFzjxJ1REH/9k=' /%3e%3c/svg%3e\" width=\"320\" alt=\"Configuring which catalogs to show in the content editor\" data-srcset=\"/assets/static/new-catalog-config.b82b75d.574c4de8aa99c13ed2f8ab0b0366b9c0.jpg 320w\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 320px) 100vw, 320px\" data-src=\"/assets/static/new-catalog-config.b82b75d.574c4de8aa99c13ed2f8ab0b0366b9c0.jpg\"><noscript><img class=\"g-image g-image--lazy g-image--loaded\" src=\"/assets/static/new-catalog-config.b82b75d.574c4de8aa99c13ed2f8ab0b0366b9c0.jpg\" width=\"320\" alt=\"Configuring which catalogs to show in the content editor\"></noscript></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Searching for Product Images</strong></p>\n<p>  When adding images to a product in Business Tools, the UI searches for an image in the media library.\nIf you don't know the exact name or how it is nested within sub-folders, you can use a wildcard (*) to help find the image.</p>\n<p>  For example, <code>*image1*</code> will match <code>/folder/image1_01</code>. This is very useful as you don't need to remember the full path of\nthe image to find it.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Control Enforce HTTPS for your Store</strong></p>\n<p>By default, SSL is enabled on your store. To configure it, update <em>Enforce SSL</em> on the store configuration item:\n<code>/sitecore/Commerce/Commerce Control Panel/Storefront Settings/Storefronts/YOURSTOREFRONT/Storefront Configuration</code>\n<em>Note: Replace YOURSTOREFRONT with your store name.</em></p>\n</li>\n</ol>\n<br />\n<h3 id=\"future-feature-requests\"><a href=\"#future-feature-requests\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"icon icon-link\"></span></a>Future feature requests</h3>\n<p>From my brief time with Sitecore Experience Commerce 9, it would be nice to see the following features added\nto make life a bit easier:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>\n<p><strong>More configuration parameters in the PowerShell script</strong></p>\n<p>For example, the URL of commerce business tools and the install directory currently need copy/pasting\nthrough various SIF config files. Making things more configurable at the top level PowerShell script\nremoves duplication.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>More interactive image search</strong></p>\n<p>Searching for images by name isn't very friendly to people managing the catalog. Having a more interactive\nsearch with a tree view of the media folder with previews of the images would help a lot.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Category Product Search</strong></p>\n<p>There's currently a search at the top level of the merchandising area. It would be good to have this\npersisted at category level.</p>\n</li>\n</ol>\n","tags":[{"title":"sitecore","path":"/tag/sitecore/"}],"references":[],"path":"/7-tips-to-get-started-with-sitecore-commerce-9/"}},"context":{}}